      "identifier": "importer_critical_publish_suppressed",
      "summary": "Critical publish errors in importer request failure path are logged but do not fail the request path",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`failUploadRequest` calls `publishImportError` and `publishImportStatus(\"aborted\")` but only logs warnings when those return errors.",
        "After those warning-only logs, `failUploadRequest` returns only `sendUploadResponse(...)` result, so publish failures cannot reach the caller as a hard failure.",
        "Several callers (`validateUploadRequest`, chunk validation, upload pipeline errors) treat any non-nil return from `failUploadRequest` as path success for response writing."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split publisher helpers into explicit policy channels (e.g., `publishImportErrorCritical` returning hard failures and `publishImportErrorBestEffort` swallowing only telemetry-only failures), and update `failUploadRequest` to propagate critical publish failures instead of always returning only response-write failure.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "error_policy_encoding_drift"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "broadcast_state_stale_on_collector_failure",
      "summary": "Broadcast loop ignores collector errors and serves stale ship state instead of exposing failure consistently",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/state.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/loop.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`bootstrapBroadcastStateWithRuntime` fails hard when `constructPierInfoWithRuntime` returns error.",
        "`runBroadcastTickWithRuntime` logs `Unable to build pier info` and substitutes `stateRuntime.GetState().Urbits` instead of failing or marking state as degraded.",
        "That means the same error type can fail startup in one path and be silently tolerated in the normal loop path, with no explicit degraded/error transition."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define one explicit behavior for collector failure in broadcast runtime (e.g., propagate error to loop supervisor, or emit a dedicated `broadcast-error` transition and freeze updates), and reuse it in both bootstrap and tick paths so clients can distinguish stale vs authoritative state.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "error_policy_encoding_drift"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Implicit error policy is encoded in function naming/patterns (`BestEffort` wrappers, ad-hoc logging-and-continue) rather than explicit interfaces or result contracts.",
      "Inconsistent failure semantics for the same operation across lifecycle boundaries (startup vs steady-state loops)."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "Importer phase status/publish drops with only warning logs and no caller-visible failure",
      "Broadcast clients receive stale pier/runtime state during upstream collector outages"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": [
      "Some upload transition publishes may be intentionally telemetry-only and expected to be non-fatal if event fan-out is degraded",
      "Transient broadcast collector hiccups might be intentionally masked to avoid transient UI instability"
